verbose_text: Studies of bone turnover markers showed an elevated alkaline phosphatase (ALP) level (210 IU/L; normal range : 47-138 IU/L), an elevated bone specific ALP level (56.97 mug/L; normal range : 11.4-24.6 mug/L), and a decreased collagen type I C-telopeptide (0.242 ng/mL; normal range : 0.299-0.573 ng/mL).
